{
  "text": "The isolated bacteria were pink to red when supplemented with selenate which was due to the accumulation of elemental selenium. This was an indication that selenate was reduced. Hunter et al., (2009) also observed red colonies indicating the formation of elemental red selenium as a reduction product of selenate in Pseudomonas sp. CA5 [CITATION_1] .",
